Sentencas: Rare-earth site high entropy double perovskite oxides with different molar ratios have been evaluated as the cathodes for intermediate -temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFC).
Titulo: High entropy double perovskite cathodes with enhanced activity and operational stability for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effect of configuration entropy on crystal structure, electrical conductivity, electrochemical performance and stability are investigated.
Titulo: High entropy double perovskite cathodes with enhanced activity and operational stability for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Our results reveal that the activity of all high entropy oxides show enhanced electrochemical activity.
Titulo: High entropy double perovskite cathodes with enhanced activity and operational stability for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Among them, the equimolar one (HEO) exhibits the highest activity with a low polarization resistance of 0.05 omega cm(2) at 700(degrees)C. Moreover, it exhibits excellent stability in the CO2-containing atmosphere.
Titulo: High entropy double perovskite cathodes with enhanced activity and operational stability for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The enhanced activity and operational stability can be attributed to reduced surface Ba segregation and the formation of active and robust BaCoO3-delta nanoparticles on HEO surface, rather than BaCO3 and Co(3)O(4 )phases.
Titulo: High entropy double perovskite cathodes with enhanced activity and operational stability for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This work indicates that configurational entropy engineering is very effective for rational surface composition regulation.
Titulo: High entropy double perovskite cathodes with enhanced activity and operational stability for solid oxide fuel cells
